    <name>
      <text>Solving a linear system using inverse method</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Given that \(
\left\{ \begin{array}{r}
{@a1*x_1+b1*x_2@} & = {@d1@} \\
{@b2*x_2+c2*x_1@} &= {@d2@} \\

\end{array}\right.
\)</p>
<p>find&nbsp;\(x_{1}\) and&nbsp;\(x_{2}\) using Inverse method.<br></p>
<br>\({@matrix_variable@} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3><b>Worked Solution</b></h3>
<p>The system  \(
\left\{ \begin{array}{r}
{@a1*x_1+b1*x_2@} & = {@d1@} \\
{@b2*x_2+c2*x_1@} &= {@d2@} \\

\end{array}\right.
\) is given by \(Ax=B\) where \(A\) is the matrix defined by \({@matrix_A@}, x={@matrix_variable@}\) and \(B={@column_vector@}\)</p>
<p>We recall the inverse of \( A\) is \(A^{-1}={@matrix_inverse@} \). Then,</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\( Ax=B \Rightarrow A^{-1}Ax= A^{-1}B\)</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(\quad \quad \quad \quad \Rightarrow x= A^{-1}B\)</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(\quad \quad \quad \quad \Rightarrow x= \displaystyle {@matrix_inverse@}{@column_vector@}\)</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(\quad \quad \quad \quad \Rightarrow {@matrix_variable@}= \displaystyle {@ta@}\)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
